`v-model` is syntax sugar. By default, the value is a prop that has the name `value`, and it changes (two-way-binding) whenever the event `input` is emitted. 

Also, v-model is bound on the `select` element, not `option`.

Your code can be modified as such:

```lang-html
&lt;template&gt;
  &lt;select :value=&quot;value&quot; @input=&quot;clicked&quot;&gt;
    &lt;option
      v-for=&quot;option in options&quot;
      :key=&quot;option.label&quot;
      :value=&quot;option.value&quot;
    &gt;
      {{ option.label }}
    &lt;/option&gt;
  &lt;/select&gt;
&lt;/template&gt;

&lt;script&gt;
  export default {
    props: {
      value: {
        required: true
      },
      options: {
        type: Array,
        required: true
      }
    },
    methods: {
      clicked($event) {
        this.$emit(&#39;input&#39;, $event.target.value);
      }
    }
  };
&lt;/script&gt;
```

Documentation here: https://vuejs.org/v2/guide/components.html#Using-v-model-on-Components

You can also change the prop name and event name that `v-model` uses, see: https://vuejs.org/v2/guide/components-custom-events.html#Customizing-Component-v-model

