The `extend` keyword is used to augment an existing type within the same schema. For example, we can do:

```
type User {
  username: String!
}

extend type User {
  firstName: String!
  lastName: String!
}
```

This is useful when splitting your schema across multiple files or building your schema from a base schema.

You cannot, however, extend a type that doesn&#39;t exist. You have no defined a `Query` type in your schema, so you cannot extend it. Just remove the `extend` keyword.

