Here is a simple PHP script which can be used to isolate `21.3` from the JavaScript string:

    $input = &quot;last_value\u0022:21.3,\u0022last_value_time&quot;;
    $parts = explode(&quot;\\&quot;, $input);
    $num = preg_match(&quot;/(\d+\.\d+)\D*$/&quot;, $parts[1], $matches);
    echo $matches[1];

The idea is to first split on path separator `\`.  Then, use a regex match on the second path to isolate the number you want.

